Description: Wooden key with small knob finial, two square-sectioned teeth and a circular dowel tooth set in a hole drilled right through the key. This is a repair after the square tooth has been removed. Decorated with incised parallel grooves and 'X's. The circular dowel is broken off where it projects from the key.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Qasr Ibrim (Nubia), LC1-22 Room 1 upper fill
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 2003 10 Apr-31 Aug, Barcelona, CaixaForum, Nubia: Los reinos del Nilo en Sudan 2003/4 23 Sep-4 Jan, Madrid, Sala de Exposiciones de la Fundacio, Nubia: Los reinos del Nilo en Sudan
Acquisition name: Division of Finds: Egyptian Antiquities Organisation
